JDBC: (Java Database Connectivity)(Specification)
JDBC api (java.sql) (Connection, PreparedStatement, Statement,CallableStatement, ResutlSet, DriverManger)
jdbc auto commit default feature( Transaction management)
Jdbc Exception are checked exceptions.
jdbc will support all the dabase vendors(Mysql, MSSQL, ORacle...etc...(RDBMS-->SQL-->))
3. JDBC 4 types drivers for connecting the dabases
	1. JDBC-ODBC driver, 2. Native API driver, 3. Network Protocal API driver, 4. Thin Driver

4. five steps are there 
	1. register the database driver
	2. create the connection object by using drviermanager class
	3. create the statemnt object
	4. execute the queries
	5. close the connection
	
	

	
executeQuery() for getting data , executeUpdate() for storing, updating, deleting 

6. autoCommit

7. CallableStatement

